{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place water, sugar and yeast in mixing bowl then warm <nobr>2 min\/37°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Leave to stand for 20 minutes.","Add rye flour, plain flour, rye grains, sunflower seeds, pumpkin seeds, linseeds, buttermilk, beer and salt then, with aid of spatula, mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Knead <nobr>5 min\/<\/nobr>.","Transfer to a large bowl, cover with cling film and set aside at room temperature for 24 hours (see tip).","After this time, preheat oven to 180°C and line a loaf tin (900 g\/2 lb) with baking paper. Transfer rested batter to prepared tin. Sprinkle surface with water then scatter with oats. Bake for 1 hour 45 minutes (180°C).","Remove from tin and pull away baking paper, then leave to cool completely on a wire rack before slicing and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["350 g water, plus extra for sprinkling","30 g sugar","2 tsp dried instant yeast","300 g rye flour","100 g plain flour","300 g rye grains, cracked","100 g sunflower seeds","80 g pumpkin seeds","50 g linseeds","220 g buttermilk","180 g dark beer","2 tsp fine sea salt","1 Tbsp rolled oats, for sprinkling"]}],"id":"r278589","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-D7iPn6cxjPI\/XZWqPd792VI\/AAAAAAAAfVI\/vDkK48nzzbM55O8dZOpHD0x6S9ZttEmRwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_GGns77YHJQ7NrTWu.png","title":"Scandinavian Rye Bread","publishedAt":"2018-01-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.7 g","fat":"6 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"28.2 g","calories":"866 kJ \/ 206 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, cling film, loaf tin (900 g\/2 lb), baking paper, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["The finished loaf will be more sour the longer you leave it in <nobr>step 4.<\/nobr> Can be left for up to <nobr>48 hours.<\/nobr>","Store in the fridge, or freeze until needed."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","27h","20 slices"]}